    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Luis Robert Jr.** anchoring the offensive outlook. With an efficiency score of 73.74, he is our strongest play, benefiting significantly from a favorable platoon matchup against Eduardo Rodriguez. The 14% boost from this platoon advantage, combined with Rodriguez's 4.48 xERA, creates an ideal environment for **Luis Robert Jr.** to anchor our production. **Jorge Polanco** also draws a strong assignment (63.80) against the same pitcher; while he faces a slight park downgrade, the L-on-L dynamic and his projected #3 spot in the order make him an essential high-floor asset for today\u2019s accumulation.\n\nThe remaining roster spots see **Miguel Vargas** (60.08), **Jacob Wilson** (59.85), and **Jackson Merrill** (57.92) hovering in the high-marginal to strong territory. **Miguel Vargas** gets a slight lift from wind conditions, though we are tracking Seth Lugo\u2019s ability to limit stolen bases, which creates a minor cap on his overall ceiling. The most difficult decision rested with **Liam Hicks**, who barely missed the cut with a 38.51 score. While his platoon advantage against the right-handed Lowder was tempting, the aggressive penalty for facing an elite arm (1.64 xERA) correctly relegated him to the bench to preserve our valuable game caps. \n\nManagement is currently monitoring \"Lineup Pending\" statuses for all starters, specifically looking for confirmation on **Miguel Vargas**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Jacob Wilson**, and **Luis Robert Jr.** as they slot into the top half of their respective orders. With **Gunnar Henderson**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Andy Pages** idle today due to team scheduling, the burden of maintaining our competitive edge in the 5x5 categories falls squarely on this group. We are avoiding any unnecessary risk by sitting **Liam Hicks** against a top-tier pitching matchup, choosing to prioritize efficiency over volume as we navigate the early April schedule.",
